      "Remaining equipment returned to service"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 21, 2023, at 0930 hours, a Variable Frequency Device A (VFD-A) failed at the Perdido Spar platform. The B-phase reactor of the VFD-A failed to ground, releasing smoke that activated smoke detectors in the Subsea Motor Control Center room. This triggered an automated facility shut-in and personnel muster. The Fire Team responded but found no active fire, only smoke. Cabinet A reached 350°F and was isolated from service. Estimated damage cost was $65,000. No injuries or pollution occurred.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Siemens to investigate why the reactor thermal switch did not trip the drive on over temperature"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "VFD-A failed",
      "B-phase reactor failed to ground",
      "smoke detectors activated",
      "automated facility shut-in",
      "reactor thermal switch did not trip"
    ]
